DataElement.preferredName: Nucleotide Sequence Chromosome Location Genome Assembly Sequence java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The sequence of nucleotide residues along an RNA or DNA chain.:One of the bodies in the cell nucleus that is the bearer of genes, has the form of a delicate chromatin filament during interphase, contracts to form a compact cylinder segmented into two arms by the centromere during metaphase and anaphase stages of cell division, and is capable of reproducing its physical and chemical structure through successive cell divisions.:A position, site, or point in space where something can be found._An annotated assembly of genome sequences created by the assimilation of data pieces from numerous sources._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
